          <td> 
            <div align="center"><b>The Howling Stones, key to Charisis</b></div>
          </td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr> 
    <td> 
      <table width="100%" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#EAD19F" bordercolor="#660000">
        <tr> 
          <td colspan="2" valign="top"> 
            <p><b>This Quest results in a key labeled "<img src="m1081.gif" width="20" height="20">Key 
              to Charisis", which is actually the key to the Howling Stones.</b></p>
            <p><b>There is a froglok named Durgaz in the Swamp of No Hope who 
              wants a Jade Chodakai prod and a Xalgozian fang, and in return will 
              give you a key to his master's lair.</b></p>
            <p><b>*Note*<br>
              How to do this part of the Quest if you have bad Faction with the 
              froglok.<br>
              wolf-form works. If your KOS to Durgaz, get a Druid to cast wolf-form 
              on you. The crucial part of this is making sure you go through with 
              the prompts to receive the quest - not just hand in the items. Ask 
              all the rights questions up to the details about the spell components 
              (prod and fang) and then hand them in. </b></p>
          </td>
          <td width="15%" valign="top"><a href="http://www.tapr.org/%7EOutridersKarana/kunark/swamp.html"><img src="../maps/tumb/Swamp_of_No_Hope.sm" width="150" height="202" border="0"></a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
          <td colspan="2" valign="top"> 
            <p><b>The <a href="http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/item.html?item=743">Jade 
              Chodakai Prod</a> drops from the <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=3989">Chancellor 
              of Di'Zok</a>. This shaman can be found deep within the Sarnak fortress 
              in the Lake of Ill Omen.</b></p>
            <p> <b>He (level 40) is a fair bit stronger than the rest of the many 
              Sarnaks in the area. Spawn time 2-1/2 hours about..</b></p>
          </td>
          <td width="15%" valign="top"><a href="http://www.tapr.org/%7EOutridersKarana/kunark/illomen.html"><img src="../maps/tumb/Lake_of_ILL_Omen.sm" width="150" height="154" border="0"></a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td colspan="2" valign="top">
            <p><b>The <a href="http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/item.html?item=692">Xalgozian 
              Fang</a> drops from <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=4315">Xalgoz</a> 
              located deep in the ruins of Kaesora. </b></p>
            <p><b>Hes a level 40 Necromancer , Spawn times are 30 minutes for 
              Xalgoz and his PH. 15 minutes for all the mobs around him. </b></p>
          </td>
          <td width="15%" valign="top"><a href="../maps/kaesora2.gif"><img src="../maps/tumb/kaesora2s.gif" width="150" height="178" border="0"></a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
          <td colspan="2" valign="top"> 
            <p><b>The /loc of Howling Stones (p0 x p1000) from <a href="../maps/overthere4.jpg">The 
              Overthere</a> zone </b></p>
            </td>
          <td width="15%" valign="top"><a href="../maps/howlingstones.jpg"><img src="../maps/tumb/howlingstoness.jpg" width="150" height="105" border="0"></a></td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </td>
  </tr>
